text.section:
The seller shall promptly supply the buyer under the retail charge agreement with a statement as of the end of each monthly period, which need not be a calendar month, or other regular period agreed upon in writing by the seller and the buyer, in which there is any unpaid balance thereunder, which statement shall recite the following:
The unpaid balance under the retail charge agreement at the beginning and at the end of the period;
Unless otherwise furnished by the seller to the buyer by sales slip, memorandum, or otherwise, a description or identification of the goods or services purchased during the period, the cash sale price and the date of each purchase;
The payments made by the buyer to the seller and any other credits to the buyer during the period;
The amount, if any, of any time price differential for such period; and
A legend to the effect that the buyer may at any time pay his total unpaid balance or any part thereof.
